Program: Discovery
Title: What remains to be discovered - cosmology
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry9s
Last Broadcast Date: 08 January 2003
The first programme looks outward into space and looks at what we know about the universe. How the biggest telescopes on earth and in space can survey the universe on the largest scales, revealing its structure and the powerful forces which shape it. But there remain many, many unanswered questions.